# EAS Build: this file lives at mobile/.easignore and, per gitignore
# semantics, every pattern below is interpreted relative to THIS directory
# — mobile/ — NOT the repo root. A leading `/` anchors to mobile/, which
# is why the previous version wrongly excluded mobile/package.json (the
# one EAS actually needs). Build 1.0.2 (9) on 2026-04-21 failed with
# "package.json does not exist in /home/expo/workingdir/build/mobile"
# exactly because of that misunderstanding.
#
# Original goal (still valid): keep the Next.js web app (which sits at
# ../src, ../public, etc. relative to this file) out of the EAS archive
# so the Linux builder's tar doesn't choke on dynamic-route folder names
# like src/app/api/hotels/pending/[ref]/.
#
# Fix: use unanchored, name-based patterns. gitignore matches any
# occurrence of a named directory anywhere in the archive tree, so
# `src/` catches the web app's src/ whether EAS archives from git root
# or mobile/. No leading `/` — that way mobile/'s own files are safe.

# --- Next.js web app directories (match by name, anywhere) ---
src/
public/
docs/
scripts/
.next/
out/
coverage/
build/

# --- Next.js / web app config files by name (not anchored) ---
# These filenames don't exist inside mobile/, so name-matching is safe.
next.config.js
next.config.ts
next.config.mjs
next-env.d.ts
tailwind.config.js
tailwind.config.ts
postcss.config.js
postcss.config.mjs
middleware.ts
middleware.js
flights.json
offer.json
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md

# NOTE: Intentionally NOT excluding package.json, package-lock.json,
# tsconfig.json, vercel.json, or README.md — mobile/ has its own copies
# of these and EAS needs them. The repo-root versions getting into the
# archive is harmless (a few extra KB; EAS builds from mobile/ anyway).

# --- Always-excluded ---
node_modules/
.vercel/
.env
.env.*
.claude/
.expo/
*.tsbuildinfo
*.log
